TY  - JOUR
AU  - Becker, Bo
AU  - Campello, Murillo
AU  - Thell, Viktor
AU  - Yan, Dong
T1  - Credit risk, debt overhang, and the life cycle of callable bonds
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfae001
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 28
IS  - 3
SP  - 945
EP  - 985
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We show that callable bonds have both higher yields and lower market prices than matched non-callable bonds of the same issuer-time, reflecting the value of call features to issuers and investors. This “value of callability” as well as the inclusion and the exercise of call rights are jointly determined by issuer credit quality. Critically, our agency-based theoretical and empirical analyses show that callability reduces debt overhang in corporate mergers. Our results help explain the value and increasing prevalence of callable bonds in credit markets.
Y2  - 10/27/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfae001
ER  - 



